Dear Alex J. Hernandez.<br><br>
As I have written under the banner of comments regarding this site, and vets vs. non vets. I suggest you read those and see my answer to you.  I never was one to call vets baby killers, rather I did my best, risked my life, to try and educate you, and your brothers, not to go.  I think the picture you describe is incredibe and wrong, but it happened to you and I can't erase it. Nor can I erase napalm and burning civilians.  Bottom line:  the war was wrong, the protestors right, and we all were victims, burned and non burned alike, the difference, however, is the pain, physical and psychological. I have given 20years of my life towards helping those heal the psych pain, i doubt the burn units ever saw the real victims in &quot;the country&quot; that were torched.  Nice that now, when we are save, 30 years later, we can talk.  Check out Tom's home page and add to it.<br><br>
Dr. Crazy (to my friends) and &quot;check your six&quot; as I have learned from this site.
